# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in your key.
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The AI features (hover explanations, figure walkthroughs) need a provider
# key. Everything else — highlights, outline, find-in-page — works without
# one. An env key takes precedence over the in-app AI setup and disables it.
# Providers are checked in the order below; set exactly one.

# Anthropic (Claude). Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# OpenRouter — one key, many models, including free ones. Get a key at
# https://openrouter.ai/keys. The base URL is built in. Recommended model is
# the free router "openrouter/free", which auto-picks a free model and routes
# image requests (figure walkthroughs) to a vision-capable one. Free models
# are capped at 20 requests/minute (and 1000/day once you've bought $10 of
# credits), shared across all users — the app surfaces a friendly "busy"
# notice when that cap is hit.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=openrouter/free

# OpenAI (or any OpenAI-compatible endpoint). Optionally set a base URL and
# model; the model defaults to gpt-4o-mini.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=
# OPENAI_MODEL=

# Optional: where uploaded PDFs, the render cache, and reader.db live.
# Defaults to ./backend/data. Uncomment to override.
# PDF_READER_DATA_DIR=./data
